==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: meaningful
<hw>meaningful</hw> <pos>adj.</pos> <def>Having a meaning or purpose;
having significance; <as>as, a <ex>meaningful</ex> explanation; a
<ex>meaningful</ex> discussion; a <ex>meaningful</ex> pause; to live a
<ex>meaningful</ex> life</as>. Opposite of <ant>meaningless</ant>.</def>
[Narrower terms: <stype>comprehensible, understandable</stype>;
<stype>indicative, significative, suggestive </stype>; <stype>meaty,
substantive </stype>; <stype>purposeful</stype>] <see>Also See:
<er>purposeful</er>, <er>significant</er>, <er>important</er>.</see>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>meaningfulness</ent>⟦br⟧
